def: A man who keeps ward; a guard. [R.] Sydney Smith.
A peduncle rising from the ground or from a subterranean stem,as in the stemless violets, the bloodroot, and the like.
Pertaining to typhoid fever and malaria; as, typhomalarialfever, a form of fever having symptoms both of malarial and typhoidfever.

A European gold wasp (Chrysis ignita) which has the under sideof the abdomen bright red, and the other parts deep bluish green witha metallic luster. The larva is parasitic in the nests of other waspsand of bees.
The act or process of subliming, or the state or result ofbeing sublimed.
To dig out of the ground; to take out of a place of burial; todisinter. Mantell.
In a punctual manner; promptly; exactly.
Of certain achromatic lenses, having the same focus for theactinic and for the brightest of the visual rays.
A segment forming a side piece in the head of a cask. Knight.
A condition of impoverishment of the blood; a morbid state inwhich the red corpuscles, or other important elements of the blood,are deficient.
